rComments: Alain is a sweet guy who genuinely cares about his students. He makes sure to have a good class average where everyone understands. The class however is very unorganized and test questions can sometimes be a surprise. They require critical thinking and application. ALOT easier than BPS2110 with Ogilvy. You do have to memorize as well as understand.

Dr. Musende is without a doubt among the best professors I've had during university. He is kind, knowledgeable, and his lectures are very interesting. He is an exceptional human being and mentor who allows you to reap what you sow. Personally, one of the most exciting classes to attend as he is actively involved at high levels in industry.

He is very caring but is not a good lecturer. Came late to class, went off topic every lecture, barley covered 10 slides in the 1.5 hours. Midterm/Final were not a good representation of the class, told us there would be calculations but never gave us any examples. Overall, material is interesting but the course is not structured at all.

He gets off topic a lot. Often we would only cover 10 slides each class. He starts class with an inspirational quote. The material is easy. You don't need to go to class to learn. there's a millionaire game that counts as participation 10%. I would go for participation and study the material at home, got an A- on the midterm. 40% midterm 50% exam.

Pretty sure the good review are written by him Do NOT take this class if you want a good grade. Cancels class, talks about himself majority of the time, went through only 3 lectures up until the midterm. The midterm was barley based on the lecture notes, majority were calculation type questions which no examples were given in class or in notes.

Go to class - not because you absolutely have to in order to pass this course, but because he's the best lecturer I've had in my entire undergrad. Very reasonable amount of material taught per class. His focus is on understanding, not memorization - so ask questions, participate, and you'll crush this class and love it.

Awesome Professor and an amazing human being. I loved his class, his teaching method and his enthusiasm about the topics. A little tip is to show up to class and to participate. He honestly wants all students to do well and he tries his best to make you understand the material while relating it to real life examples related to the pharma industry.

This man is so sweet. He really cares about his students. I was in a bad place when I took his class but he inspired me to keep going and be passionate about what I learn. His class is a little tricky, his notes won't make too much sense unless you go to class, but the material is easy to learn. This is my 2nd class with him. Great man!!

Dr. Musende is an inspiration. I cannot stress how much participation is important in his class. He keeps track of your participation, and will give you the academic benefit-of-the-doubt if you do so!
Dr. Musende is very knowledgeable on the topic, and conveys the material well. Participation is a huge part of class, and his exams are very fair. Would take again!
An amazing prof. Very engaging and although the matter is pretty advanced, he's always available to help. Participate!

Amazing professor! Very knowledgeable and passionate about the course material. His questions really make you think critically about the course material as opposed to pure memorization. Gives excellent feedback. Would definitely recommend him!

Hahaha, this guyyyyyy. Found it really impossible to follow him in class. Would start a thought... trail off... and never come back. So don't sweat the awful notes you'll come out with. The slides, though confusing, should be sufficient - memorize the heck out of them and you'll get an A. Very fair testing.
He kept saying don't learn that by heart but exams are nothing but learning by heart. hated him.

Very kind human being. You won't find many people better than him. Although I didn't learn much in his class, and his notes are a little bit hard to decipher he tries to make you a critical thinker by asking out of the box questions during the lectures and is very entertaining. Highly recommended.

Very good prof. He clearly cares about what he is teaching and is passionate in his lectures, easy to listen to and asks you good question worth easy bonus points. Also free candy if you answer questions!
Very enthusiast professor. Passionate about what he does and cares about his students. No textbook, just slides, and gives out a ton of candy during lectures.
